  he   spring-boot-actuator   module provides all of Spring Boot&#8217;s production-ready features.
  The recommended way to enable the features is to add a dependency on the  spring-boot-starter-actuator  &#8220;Starter&#8221;. 
   
   
   
   Definition of Actuator 
   
   An actuator is a manufacturing term that refers to a mechanical device for moving or controlling something.
  Actuators can generate a large amount of motion from a small change. 
   
   
   
   
   To add the actuator to a Maven-based project, add the following &#8216;Starte
